lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2189  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Background: This paper studies neurons of the thalamic reticular nucleus. The authors use a pharmacological and channel properties charaterization approach to show that fast GABAergic IPSCs in RTN neurons are mediated by GABAARs that contain the beta1 subunit.\n\nFig.1: Different populations of RTN neurons are recognized that show fast or slow channel decay kinetics.\nFig.4+5: Neurons with fast and slow decay kinetics can be differentiated based on their sensitivity to beta2/3 subunit selective agent loreclezole. Neurons with fast decay kinetics are loreclezole-insensitive and are presumed to have the beta1 subunit.\nFig.6: Cells that have fast decay kinetics express the beta1 subunit\nFig.7: Cells that express the beta1 subunit have fast decay kinetics\n\nAuthors conclude that fast GABAergic IPSCs in RTN neurons are mediated by GABAARs that contain the beta1 subunit.. Experimental description: \"Thalamic slices were obtained from Sprague-Dawley rats (of either sex) ranging ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2189" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

